    "body": "That's not an easy question to answer (and also not really worth an issue here, better to ask these questions to the ethereum stackexchange).\r\nWhen receiving a transaction over the wire, the transaction gets decoded in RLP and added to the txpool.\r\nI suspect you want to do some frontrunning/MEV stuff. The place you're looking for is here: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/tx_pool.go \r\nThe txpool tracks all transactions that are not yet executed.",
